Ingredients
- Masa harina
- Salt
- Water
  
Instructions
- Mix two cups masa harina with 1.5 cups hot water and a pinch of salt until combined. 
- Knead dough for a couple minutes. Add water or masa harina if it is too dry or too wet. It should not crumble, nor be sticky. 
- Let rest for 20 minutes covered with a damp towel
- Roll the dough into balls the size of golf balls 
- Using a tortilla press or something large and flat with wax or parchment paper on each side of the dough, press the balls into tortillas
- Heat a griddle or pan, and once hot, cook the tortillas for 1-2 minutes on each side until they brown slightly
- Enjoy the tortillas
